This paper deals with the problem of robotic navigation, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The authors use reinforcement learning and deep $Q$-networks, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves testing the learned policies on different versions of the environment, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) or control systems (cs.SY).
